reviews.review_text: that you chris chappel, of "the core" chevy chase here! a must,, was my 14th bootleg back in 1980,,, when i got on the bus,,, no wonder,,,dude Sick bits indeed i cranked this on my way down to lyon,france,, think i'm the only one in this country to groove to the dead,,, 30 years later peacetrain, spreads peace

a bit overrated I do think this show has some special moments and certainly a desire, but it really just doesn't seem as 'on' as so many others. But so many love this one (as do so many the cornell 77).

Sugaree I give this show five stars on the Sugaree alone. The only problem with giving reviews is you can't hear the show while writing a review. If I could keep listening to the show while writing a review, I would probably give a lot more reviews. But hey, it's a Dead show. Most people that have a recording of a Dead show aren't going to post it if its NOT a decent recording. The usual question is were they having a good night or a GREAT night. It's rare that they had a bad night, although I'm sure those nights did occur, I can't really say that I've heard any of them.
